Program: A History of Ideas
Title: Historian Justin Champion on Toleration
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b062kdd7
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 21 Jul 2015
Professor Justin Champion examines Locke's theory of Toleration through the inhabitants of Spitalfields past and present. He goes to Brick Lane whose famous mosque was built as a Huguenot Church and became a synagogue before becoming the centre of Bengali life in London. He meets the Bishop of London, himself of Huguenot descent and local politician Abdal Ullah to discuss religious tolerance then and now Producer: Maggie Ayre. Show less